  "prompt": "What is the meaning of Hindi words 'Shubh' and 'Laabh'?",
  "response": "In Hindi, the word \"Shubh\" (\u0936\u0941\u092d) means \"auspicious,\" \"good,\" or \"fortunate.\" It is often used in contexts related to positive events, blessings, and favorable circumstances.\n\nThe word \"Laabh\" (\u0932\u093e\u092d) means \"benefit,\" \"profit,\" or \"gain.\" It refers to any advantage or positive outcome that one gains from a situation, action, or investment.\n\nTogether, \"Shubh Laabh\" (\u0936\u0941\u092d \u0932\u093e\u092d) is a common phrase used in various contexts, especially in festive or auspicious occasions, signifying a wish for good fortune and benefit.",
